message.content:
1. Linear mixed-effect regression models were used in the study.
2. The study aimed to estimate the effect of CPT on feelings of perceived and internalized stigma.
3. The study also aimed to estimate the effect of CPT on felt stigma.
4. The study investigated whether felt stigma and discrimination moderated the effects of CPT.
5. The moderation effects of felt stigma and discrimination were examined on combined depression and anxiety symptoms.
6. The moderation effects of felt stigma and discrimination were examined on posttraumatic stress.
7. The moderation effects of felt stigma and discrimination were examined on functional impairment.

messages.content:
Statement: Linear mixed-effect regression models were used to estimate (1) the effect of CPT on feelings of perceived and internalized (felt) stigma, and (2) whether felt stigma and discrimination (enacted stigma) moderated the effects of CPT on combined depression and anxiety symptoms, posttraumatic stress, and functional impairment.
